[src:1112/1039] Year **1039** (**MXXXIX**) was a common year starting on Monday of the Julian calendar.
[src:1112/1040] Year **1040** (**MXL**) was a leap year starting on Tuesday of the Julian calendar.
[src:1112/1050] Year **1050** (**ML**) was a common year starting on Monday of the Julian calendar.
[src:1112/1054] Year **1054** (**MLIV**) was a common year starting on Saturday of the Julian calendar.
[src:1112/1054] East-West schism: the ongoing break of communion between the Roman Catholic and Eastern Orthodox churches.
[src:1112/1060] Year **1060** (**MLX**) was a leap year starting on Saturday of the Julian calendar.
[src:1112/1060] It was the 1060th year of the Common Era (CE) and Anno Domini (AD) designations, the 60th year of the 2nd millennium, the 60th year of the 11th century, and the first year of the 1060s decade.
[src:1112/1075] Year **1075** (**MLXXV**) was a common year starting on Thursday of the Julian calendar.
[src:1112/1112] Year **1112** (**MCXII**) was a leap year starting on Monday of the Julian calendar.
